UNICEF aims to achieve this through Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. description.narrative: 97,000 children gained access to online learning during school closure with direct support in collaboration with Ministries of Education and Notes Master (a registered Digital Public Good) pathfinder. 375 teachers and curriculum developers were trained and/or developed digital content. This finalised 6,910 curriculum-based digital content (2,907 for Primary and 4,003 for secondary subjects) across Trinidad and Tobago, Barbados, Turks and Caicos Islands, Grenada, Antigua and Barbuda and Dominica out of 23,183 planned, with the remaining planned for completion in July 2022. UNICEF supported 22,500 vulnerable children with the provision of devices in collaboration with OECS, GPE, and Generation Unlimited funds.;; | Status:On-track | As-of Date:17/01/2022
